rComments: The course was interesting and his lectures were very engaging. I actually sat in on one of the JAL328 lectures the year before I took it and it wasn't as good, so he obviously learned from his semester of experience. If you want to do well you have to know both the LIN and ANT stuff. Make sure your test/assignment answers are all specific.

This was his first year teaching a course, so he frequently ran out of time during lectures. He gave us supplementary material before quizzes and tests, but always posted them later than told.  He truly likes the material, and will respond to your emails quickly.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: You can pass the tests with just the lecture slides or just the readings, but you'll need to really understand the material to ace them. That said, his tests are not unfair; it's just that he tests for knowledge, rather than no-brainer multiple choice. You need to retain and understand the info. This course is not hard, but it's not for the lazy.
